API Reference

AbstractModel.jl API reference.

model.jl

Model

AbstractModel.Initialize — Function
Initialize(input_data::OrderedDict)

Function to initialize the model based on given input data. This function calls functions initializing the solver, model, etc.

Arguments

  • input_data::OrderedDict: Dictionary containing data used to build the model.

Examples

'''julia-repl julia> modelcontents = Initialize(inputdata); "constraint" => ... "expression" => ... "variable" => ... "tuple" => ... "genconstraint" => ... "genexpression" => ... "res_dir" => ... "model" => ... '''

AbstractModel.solve_model — Function
solve_model(model_contents::OrderedDict)

Function to solve model.

Arguments

  • model_contents::OrderedDict: Dictionary containing all data and structures used in the model.

Examples

'''julia repl julia> Predicer.solvemodel(modelcontents); '''
